    <h1>UNO Unblocked — Play Free Online, No Download</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">A browser-based UNO card game that runs anywhere a browser runs. Nothing to install, no account to create.</p>

    <h2>Why This Version Works Almost Anywhere</h2>
    <p>Play UNO Free is a plain website — not an app, not a download, not a browser extension. If you can open a web page, you can play. There's no installer to be blocked by an administrator, no app store required, and no plugin to enable.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No download or installation</strong> — the entire game runs in your browser tab</li>
      <li><strong>No signup or login</strong> — just pick a nickname and play</li>
      <li><strong>Lightweight</strong> — loads fast even on slow or shared networks</li>
      <li><strong>Works on any device</strong> — Chromebooks, laptops, phones, and tablets</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Perfect for Chromebooks</h2>
    <p>Because there's nothing to install, the game is a great fit for Chromebooks and other managed devices where installing apps isn't an option. The interface adapts to any screen size and supports both touch and mouse.</p>

    <h2>Play With Your Whole Class or Group</h2>
    <p>Up to 20 players can join a single room — enough for an entire classroom, club, or office break room. Create a private room, share the room code, and everyone joins in seconds. <a href="/20-player-uno">Learn more about 20-player games →</a></p>

    <h2>Family-Friendly by Design</h2>
    <p>There is no text chat, no user accounts, and no personal data collection. Players communicate through fun emotes only, so games stay friendly and appropriate for all ages.</p>

    <h2>A Quick Note on Network Policies</h2>
    <p>Some schools and workplaces restrict gaming sites on their networks, and those policies are up to the network administrator. We don't do anything to bypass filters — this page simply explains why a no-download browser game is accessible in more places than downloadable games.</p>

